    <fr:title text="cardinality of the disjoint sum › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00LZ/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LZ.xml" title="cardinality of the disjoint sum" addr="jms-00LZ" type="local">cardinality of the disjoint sum</fr:link> › jms-00LZ/0</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We can think of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}+{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as the set of coordinates into two strips of cells, the first of which has <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> cells and the second of which has <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> cells. Conversely, we can think of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [m+n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as the set of coordinates a single strip of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m+n]]></fr:tex> cells. A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I\colon {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}+{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\to  {\mathopen {}\left  [m+n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> could then be thought of as witnessing a method to lay out the two strips in serial; we will define such a function and show that it is a bijection.</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   I &\colon {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}+{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}} \to  {\mathopen {}\left  [m+n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\\
   I{\mathopen {}\left (0,i<m\right )\mathclose {}} &= i\\
   I{\mathopen {}\left (1,j<n\right )\mathclose {}} &= m+j
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>The function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> places a cell from the first strip sequentially after the first <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> cells of the serialised strip. The inverse can be defined as follows:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  I{\mathopen {}\left (k\right )\mathclose {}} =
  \begin {cases}
   {\mathopen {}\left (0,k\right )\mathclose {}} &\text {when } k < m\\
   {\mathopen {}\left (1,k-m\right )\mathclose {}} &\text {when } k \geq  m
  \end {cases}
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter>
